Pleased to have joined my fellow colleagues to reaffirm our support for D.C. Statehood. 

DC has a larger population than two states. Yet, these citizens do not have a vote in Congress. Today, the House passed H.R. 51 to end this injustice & bring DC residents one step closer to the representation they deserve. #DCStatehood

node.text:
Six months after the January 6th insurrection, America faces an extraordinary challenge to the fate of our Democracy. We have the duty, to the Constitution and the Country, to find the truth of the January 6th insurrection and to ensure that such an assault on our Democracy cannot again happen.

Today, the bipartisan Select Committee to Investigate the January 6th Attack on the U.S. Capitol held its first hearing. Under the leadership of Chairman Bennie Thompson, the Committee established the priority of beginning with the testimony of patriots who served and sacrificed on that dark day. To that end, we are honored by the participation on Tuesday of Harry Dunn, Private First Class, U.S. Capitol Police; Aquilino Gonell, Sergeant, U.S. Capitol Police; Michael Fanone, Officer, Metropolitan Police Department; and Daniel Hodges, Officer, Metropolitan Police Department.

Each is a hero, and brought powerful testimony about the truth of the day. Thankful for their patriotism and leadership.

Today, Democrats from both chambers of Congress joined together to celebrate a promise fulfilled. Delivering life-changing benefits for 35 million families nationwide and cutting child poverty in half, the Biden Child Tax Credit puts women and families first. President Biden and Congressional Democrats will continue to fight to make this expansion permanent as it is both an economic and a moral imperative to #BuildBackBetter.

As House Speaker, it is my official and personal honor to lead this distinguished group of Members to pay tribute to our beloved colleague and dear friend, the late Congressman John Lewis. John Lewis was a true warrior for freedom, who helped transform America with his unrivaled courage, patriotism and goodness.
 
It is fitting that, one year after his passing, so many of John’s friends will gather this weekend to celebrate his saintly life and to christen a naval ship bearing his name, a beautiful testament to his legacy as one of the greatest heroes of American history.
 
As the USNS John Lewis sets sail across the sea in service to our nation, may this beautiful ship be a beacon of strength and inspiration as we carry on John’s life mission: to pursue a more perfect union.
 
#GoodTrouble
